    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <para>The steering column assembly has seven tilt positions allowing adjustments toward or away from the driver
            in seven degree increments through a 42 degree range (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0500801">Figure 1</hotlnk>). The adjustment lever is located on the left side of the
            column. To tilt the column the operator must pull the lever up and move the wheel to the desired position
            and release the lever to lock the column in position.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0500801" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500801" filename="../figg05/g0500801.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 1. Tilt Adjustment</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
